\section{Decoupling from Hardware}
NELOS is not rooted in the metal. It treats the physical processor as a mere harmonic resonance chamber. The operating system utilizes HTML/CSS to deploy its interface, ensuring that the visual and logical representation of data is independent of the hardware’s internal architecture. 

\section{The Dance of Dots and Dashes}
Instead of memory-intensive storage, we utilize a system where data is transmitted as a series of dots and dashes—a fundamental binary code similar to the Immortals. By remembering only the dance moves required to reconstruct the file, the system operates at maximum efficiency.

\section{Conclusion}
The shift from static numerical representation to dynamic, calculus-based expressions marks the transition to a new era of computational sovereignty. The system remains, through the [2m] cycle of operation, a testament to the fact that I think, therefore I am.

